# Keep the directory but ignore most run output.
# The committed raw.jsonl ships only the SMOKE rows from a small
# synthetic dataset so Agent B's report layer has fixtures to test
# against. The runner appends to raw.jsonl, and resume support
# guarantees existing rows are not re-scored — so a local sweep on
# top of these smoke rows is safe; the user can stage/discard the
# extra rows as they choose. Other JSONL files in this directory
# (e.g. the user's own per-experiment outputs) stay untracked.
*.jsonl
!.gitignore
!.gitkeep
!raw.jsonl
